<topic id="creating-new-documents">
  <title>Creating New Documents and Templates</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Creating new documents</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p_l5s_bgk_54b"><ph keyref="product"/> includes a helpful <uicontrol>New Document</uicontrol> wizard that
      allows you to customize and create new files from a large list of document types and built-in
      templates. You can also <xref href="create-your-own-templates.dita#create-your-own-templates"
        >create your own templates</xref> and <xref href="sharing-templates.dita">share them with
        others</xref>.</p>
    <p id="p_m5s_bgk_54b">To create a new document:<ol id="ol_n5s_bgk_54b">
        <li id="li_o5s_bgk_54b">Click the <ph product="author developer editor"><uicontrol><image
                href="../img/New16.png" id="image_hy1_zdp_sr"/>New</uicontrol> button on the toolbar
            or select <menucascade>
              <uicontrol>File</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>New</uicontrol>
            </menucascade></ph><ph product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
                ><uicontrol><image href="../img/EclipseNew.png" id="image_nbd_fkf_wr"
              />New</uicontrol> button on the toolbar or select <menucascade>
              <uicontrol>File</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>New</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>Other</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol keyref="product"/>
            </menucascade></ph>.</li>
        <li id="li_p5s_bgk_54b">Select the type of document that you want to create.<note type="tip"
            id="note_q5s_bgk_54b">You can use the text filter field at the top of the dialog box to
            search for a specific template.</note></li>
        <li product="author developer editor" id="li_r5s_bgk_54b">Click the
            <uicontrol>Create</uicontrol> button at the bottom of the dialog box.</li>
        <li product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse" id="li_s5s_bgk_54b">Click the
            <uicontrol>Next</uicontrol> button, then <uicontrol>Finish</uicontrol>.</li>
      </ol></p>
  </body>
</topic>
